      <p>In Trimester 2, students in MS Coding and Computer Science will get experience with programming language, developing computer systems that interact with people or the environment, as well as wiring and construcing low-power electrical devices. <br>For their culminating project in Tri 2, students will develop a prototype for a device that solves on of three situations: inceasing night time safety for runners or bicyclists, beautifying a public space through interactive artwork, or dispensing food or other necessities for pets or people who may not be able to access it on their own or on a schedule.   <br><br> Curious about our Micro Bit computers or the curriculum? Visit these sites for more info: <br> <a href="http://microbit.org/"> Micro Bit</a> <br> <a href="https://www.pltw.org/our-programs/pltw-gateway-curriculum#curriculum-4">PLTW: Innovators and Makers</a></p>
